The problem that prompted this PR was actually in the retry code in #10684 with the `retry_streaming_succeeds_before_replay_finished` test.  The problem is that the call completes and the test calls `grpc_byte_buffer_destroy()` before the retried send_message op completes and we destroy the slices internally.

I think this is actually a more general problem, though.  From the application's point of view, the send_message op will complete as soon as we have enough flow control to send the message, and the application can destroy the byte buffer at that point, because the send_message op is complete.  But the byte buffer still owns the slices, because we haven't taken them away from it, and there is no guarantee at that point that we are actually done with the slices.

I think you're right that this doesn't actually have anything to do with the recv_trailing_metadata op.  It's purely a race condition in the semantics of the send_message op.
